Description
------------------

This course covers emerging telecommunications technologies and their
applications and implications for international business. The coverage will
involve issues related to economics, law, politics, international relations,
and the management of technology. The competitive environment in the U.S. will
be compared with the economic, political and technological environments of
other countries. The technolog-ical challenges in connecting users across the
globe, and current standards and protocols established by international
organizations to achieve global connectivity will be discussed.

